CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1957, pg. 12 reads: "The Frogs Entertain - The above pictures were taken at the Frogs' first affair during the club's 47th annual celebration of Frogs Week. Held Sunday at the Villa Monaco, members of the club entertained their wives and their out-of-town guests at a swank cocktail party and buffet supper.  Top left photo, left to right: Mrs. Wendell Freeland nad house guest, Miss Doris Freeland of Baltimore, Md.; Mrs. James K. Lewis, Mrs. Betty Lee Brady of Chicago; George Bolden of Philadelphia; Dr. Lewis and Mrs. George Bolden, Mrs. Earl Childs, Mrs. Robert M. Ratcliffe and Mrs. C.C. Blow are in background..."
TitMainTitle: Seated at table, from left: Mrs. Wendell Freeland, Doris Freeland, Mrs. James K. Lewis, Betty Lee Brady, George Bolden, Dr. Lewis, and Mrs. George Bolden; in background from left: Mrs. Earl Childs, Mrs. Robert M. Ratcliffe, and Mrs. C.C. Blow, gathered in Villa Monaco for the 47th Annual FROGS Week, another version
